headline: FedEx Climbs as Profit Guidance Eases Holiday Season Worries
summary: Adjusted earnings in its fiscal second quarter, which concludes at the end of November, will surpass the $4.05 a share the courier generated last year, Chief Financial Officer John Dietrich told investors Tuesday at an industry conference.  Analysts are anticipating $4.02 a share on average in estimates compiled by Bloomberg.  The comments sent FedEx shares up 5.3% as of 1:38 p.m. in New York.

headline: Is the Stock Market Open Today? Here Are the Trading Hours for Veterans Day.
summary: November is nearly halfway over—and investors have a lot to process.  Earnings from some of the biggest names in tech, including  Palantir  have started rolling in, as investors continue to grapple with concerns over high valuations.  Now, Veterans Day has arrived.

headline: Will FedEx’s (FDX) Credit Moves and Freight Spin-Off Reshape Its Long-Term Business Stability Narrative?
summary: In recent days, FedEx amended its US$3.5 billion credit agreements with major banks to prepare for the planned spin-off of FedEx Freight by June 2026 while managing operational changes after grounding its MD-11 aircraft fleet amid heightened industry safety measures. This dual focus on financial restructuring and risk response reinforces FedEx's commitment to logistics continuity and long-term business stability during a period of industry and regulatory uncertainty.
